window.docContents[153].resolve({"/____________/______--conv--___________________________/#conv-rw":{"contents":"change t' replaces the target t with t',\nassuming t and t' are definitionally equal.\n\nrw [thm] rewrites the target using thm. See the rw tactic for more information.\n\nrw [rules] applies the given list of rewrite rules to the target.\nSee the rw tactic for more information.\n\nerw [rules] is a shorthand for rw (transparency := .default) [rules].\nThis does rewriting up to unfolding of regular definitions (by comparison to regular rw\nwhich only unfolds @[reducible] definitions).\n\nThe apply thm conv tactic is the same as apply thm the tactic.\nThere are no restrictions on thm, but strange results may occur if thm\ncannot be reasonably interpreted as proving one equality from a list of others.\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009策略样张\u0009使用  conv  进行有针对性的重写\u0009改变目标","header":"14.6.4.3. 重写","id":"/____________/______--conv--___________________________/#conv-rw"},"/____________/______-Type/#zh-basictypes-h001":{"contents":"单元类型是只有一个元素的规范类型，名为 unit，并由空元组 () 表示。\n它仅描述一个值，该值由不应用于任何参数的所述构造函数组成。\n\nUnit 类似于源自 C 的语言中的 void：尽管 void 没有可命名的元素，但它表示从没有附加信息的函数返回控制流。\n在函数式编程中，Unit 是“不返回任何内容”的返回类型。\n从数学上讲，这由一个完全无信息的值表示，而不是像 Empty 这样表示无法访问的代码的空类型。\n\n当使用 monads​​ 进行编程时，Unit 特别有用。\n对于任何类型 α，m α 表示具有副作用并返回 α 类型的值的操作。\nm Unit 类型表示具有一些副作用但不返回值的操作。\n\n单位类型有两种变体：\n\n* Unit 是存在于最小非命题 宇宙 中的 Type。* PUnit 是 宇宙多态，可用于任何非命题 宇宙。\n\n在幕后，Unit 实际上被定义为 PUnit.{1}。\n如果可能，Unit 应优先于 PUnit，以避免不必要的 Universe 参数。\n如果有疑问，请使用 Unit 直到出现 Universe 错误。\n\nThe canonical type with one element. This element is written ().Unit has a number of uses:* It can be used to model control flow that returns from a function call without providing other\ninformation.* Monadic actions that return Unit have side effects without computing values.* In polymorphic types, it can be used to indicate that no data is to be stored in a particular\nfield.\n\nThe only element of the unit type.It can be written as an empty tuple: ().\n\nThe canonical universe-polymorphic type with just one element.It should be used in contexts that require a type to be universe polymorphic, thus disallowing\nUnit.The only element of the universe-polymorphic unit type.\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型","header":"20.9. 单位 Type","id":"/____________/______-Type/#zh-basictypes-h001"},"/____________/______/#string-api-build":{"contents":"Returns a new string that contains only the character c.Because strings are encoded in UTF-8, the resulting string may take multiple bytes.Examples:* String.singleton 'L' = \"L\"* String.singleton ' ' = \" \"* String.singleton '\"' = \"\\\"\"* String.singleton '𝒫' = \"𝒫\"\n\nAppends two strings. Usually accessed via the ++ operator.The internal implementation will perform destructive updates if the string is not shared.Examples:* \"abc\".append \"def\" = \"abcdef\"* \"abc\" ++ \"def\" = \"abcdef\"* \"\" ++ \"\" = \"\"\n\nAppends all the strings in a list of strings, in order.Use String.intercalate to place a separator string between the strings in a list.Examples:* String.join [\"gr\", \"ee\", \"n\"] = \"green\"* String.join [\"b\", \"\", \"l\", \"\", \"ue\"] = \"blue\"* String.join [] = \"\"\n\nAppends the strings in a list of strings, placing the separator s between each pair.Examples:* \", \".intercalate [\"red\", \"green\", \"blue\"] = \"red, green, blue\"* \" and \".intercalate [\"tea\", \"coffee\"] = \"tea and coffee\"* \" | \".intercalate [\"M\", \"\", \"N\"] = \"M |  | N\"\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009弦乐\u0009API 参考","header":"20.8.4.1. 建设中","id":"/____________/______/#string-api-build"},"/____________/______/#string-api-slice":{"contents":"A region or slice of some underlying string.A slice consists of a string together with the start and end byte positions of a region of\ninterest. Actually extracting a substring requires copying and memory allocation, while many\nslices of the same underlying string may exist with very little overhead. While this could be\nachieved by tracking the bounds by hand, the slice API is much more convenient.String.Slice bundles proofs to ensure that the start and end positions always delineate a valid\nstring. For this reason, it should be preferred over Substring.Raw.The underlying strings.The byte position of the start of the string slice.The byte position of the end of the string slice.The slice is not degenerate (but it may be empty).\n\nReturns a slice that contains the entire string.\n\nThe slice from p (inclusive) up to the end of s.\n\nThe slice from the beginning of s up to p (exclusive).\n\nA Slice.Pos s is a byte offset in s together with a proof that this position is at a UTF-8\ncharacter boundary.The underlying byte offset of the Slice.Pos.The proof that offset is valid for the string slice s.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009弦乐\u0009API 参考","header":"20.8.4.11. 字符串切片","id":"/____________/______/#string-api-slice"},"/____________/______/#zh-basictypes-char-h005":{"contents":"Converts a Nat into a Char. If the Nat does not encode a valid Unicode scalar value, '\\0' is\nreturned instead.\n\nThe character's Unicode code point as a Nat.\n\nTrue for natural numbers that are valid Unicode scalar\nvalues.\n\nConverts an 8-bit unsigned integer into a character.The integer's value is interpreted as a Unicode code point.\n\nConverts a character into a UInt8 that contains its code point.If the code point is larger than 255, it is truncated (reduced modulo 256).\n\n将字符转换为字符串有两种方法。\nChar.toString 将字符转换为仅包含该字符的单例字符串，而 Char.quote 将字符转换为相应字符文字的字符串表示形式。\n\nConstructs a singleton string that contains only the provided character.Examples:* 'L'.toString = \"L\"* '\"'.toString = \"\\\"\"\n\nQuotes the character to its representation as a character literal, surrounded by single quotes and\nescaped as necessary.Examples:* 'L'.quote = \"'L'\"* '\"'.quote = \"'\\\\\\\"'\"\n\nFrom Characters to StringsChar.toString 生成一个仅包含相关字符的字符串：#eval 'e'.toString\n\"e\"\n#eval '\\x65'.toString\n\"e\"\n#eval '\"'.toString\n\"\\\"\"\nChar.quote 生成一个包含经过适当转义的字符文字的字符串：#eval 'e'.quote\n\"'e'\"\n#eval '\\x65'.quote\n\"'e'\"\n#eval '\"'.quote\n\"'\\\\\\\"'\"\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009人物\u0009API 参考","header":"20.7.4.1. 转换","id":"/____________/______/#zh-basictypes-char-h005"},"/____________/_________/#zh-basictypes-bitvec-h009":{"contents":"Unsigned less-than-or-equal-to for bitvectors.SMT-LIB name: bvule.\n\nSigned less-than-or-equal-to for bitvectors.SMT-LIB name: bvsle.\n\nUnsigned less-than for bitvectors.SMT-LIB name: bvult.\n\nSigned less-than for bitvectors.SMT-LIB name: bvslt.Examples:* BitVec.slt 6#4 7 = true* BitVec.slt 7#4 8 = false\n\nBitvectors have decidable equality.This should be used via the instance DecidableEq (BitVec w).\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009位提供\u0009API 参考","header":"20.5.5.4. 比较","id":"/____________/_________/#zh-basictypes-bitvec-h009"},"/____________/_________/#zh-basictypes-bitvec-h018":{"contents":"\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009基本类型\u0009位提供\u0009API 参考","header":"20.5.5.10. 证明自动化","id":"/____________/_________/#zh-basictypes-bitvec-h018"},"/____________/____________/#zh-tactics-reference-h024":{"contents":"Custom cbv Rewrite Rulescbv_eval 属性将定理注册为 cbv 在尝试 方程引理 之前应用的自定义重写规则。\n该定理必须是无条件等式；一侧（通常是左侧）必须是常数的应用。← 修饰符指示 cbv 从右到左应用规则：\n\ncbv_eval自定义重写规则可用于控制 cbv 如何评估特定函数。\n例如，反转的简单定义 slowReverse 由于重复使用 List.append 而具有二次复杂度。\n通过 fastReverse 提供尾递归表征，cbv 可以有效评估 slowReverse：def slowReverse : List Nat → List Nat\n  | [] => []\n  | x :: xs => slowReverse xs ++ [x]\n\ndef fastReverse (xs : List Nat) : List Nat :=\n  go [] xs\nwhere\n  go (acc : List Nat) : List Nat → List Nat\n  | [] => acc\n  | x :: xs => go (x :: acc) xs\n\ntheorem reverse_spec_aux (xs acc : List Nat) :\n    fastReverse.go acc xs =\n      slowReverse xs ++ acc := by\n  fun_induction fastReverse.go\n    <;> grind [slowReverse]\n\n@[cbv_eval] theorem slowReverse_cbv\n    (xs : List Nat) :\n    slowReverse xs = fastReverse xs := by\n  simp [fastReverse, reverse_spec_aux]\nexample : slowReverse [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] = [5, 4, 3, 2, 1] := by\n  cbv\n\n\nOpaque Declarations for cbvcbv_opaque 属性阻止 cbv 使用其 方程引理 展开声明或展开定理。\n但是，cbv_eval 重写规则始终优先于 cbv_opaque：如果声明存在匹配的 cbv_eval 规则，则即使声明标记为 cbv_opaque，也会应用该规则。\n这允许用一组受控的评估规则替换默认的展开行为。\n\nOpaque Definitions with @[cbv_opaque]将 countdown 标记为 cbv_opaque 会阻止 cbv 展开它，因此之前由 cbv 关闭的目标现在仍未解决：def countdown (n : Nat) : List Nat :=\n  match n with\n  | 0 => [0]\n  | n + 1 => (n + 1) :: countdown n\ntermination_by n\nattribute [cbv_opaque] countdown\nexample : countdown 3 = [3, 2, 1, 0] := by\n  cbv\nunsolved goals\n⊢ countdown 3 = [3, 2, 1, 0]\n\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009策略样张\u0009策略参考\u0009按价值评估","header":"14.5.19.2. 控制  cbv  行为","id":"/____________/____________/#zh-tactics-reference-h024"}});